Gauteng Transport MEC Jacob Mamabolo is urging motorists to renew their licences and not wait for the last moment. JOHANNESBURG - It appears unlikely there'll be a further extension to the validity period of driving licences that expired during the COVID-19 lockdowns. This is despite a current backlog of over 500,000 driving licences in the system. WATCH: Backlog won't be an issue - Mbalula As the final deadline of 31 March approaches, Gauteng Transport MEC Jacob Mamabolo is urging motorists to renew their licences and not wait for the last moment.